[h1] Star Trek: Renaissance (Alpha) [/h1]

Star Trek: Renaissance is designed to capture a more authentic experience of TNG and DS9 ships, equipment and technology. It makes massive changes to the starting ships, buildable ships, the technology tree and the components available to give each major power a more unique feel.

Major changes listed below.

[h2] New Ships [/h2]

[list]
    [*] Federation: Akira Class (Heavy Cruiser)
[/list]

[h2] Starting Ships [/h2]

[list]
    [*] Federation: 3x Excelsior
    [*] Klingon: 3x K'tinga
    [*] Romulan: 2x D'deridex
    [*] Cardassian: 4x Galor
[/list]

[h2] Ship Progression [/h2]

[list]
    [*] Federation: Miranda/Excelsior (Starting) -> Galaxy -> Akira -> Intrepid -> Sovereign
    [*] Klingon: K'tinga (Starting) -> B'Rel -> K'Vort -> Vor'cha -> Negh'Var
    [*] Romulan: D'deridex (Starting) -> Ferrax -> Vindius -> Valdore -> Majestus
    [*] Cardassian: Galor (Starting) -> Hideki -> Keldon -> Kazikai -> Nokoram
[/list]

The Defiant is available as per the base game via the mission tree.

[h2] Weapon Progression [/h2]

Each power gets a unique set of weapons.

[list]
    [*] Federation: Phasers (Type VIII, IX, Type X, Type X!, Type XII) + Photon Torpedoes (Type IV, V, VI) / Quantum Torpedoes (Type I, Type II)
    [*] Klingon: Disruptors (Type I, Type II, Type III, Type IV, Type V) + Disruptor Cannons (Type I, Type II, Type III, Type IV, Type V) + Photon Torpedoes (Type IV, V, VI) / Quantum Torpedoes (Type I, Type II)
    [*] Romulan: Disruptors (Type I, Type II, Type III, Type IV, Type V) + Disruptor Cannons (Type I, Type II, Type III, Type IV, Type V) + Plasma Torpedoes (Type I, Type II, Type III, Type IV, Type V)
    [*] Cardassian: Phasers (Type VIII, IX, Type X, Type X!, Type XII) + Spiral Wave Disruptors (Type I, Type II, Type III, Type IV, Type V)
[/list]

[h2] Other [/h2]

[list]
    [*] Federation ships (aside from the Defiant class) can survey
    [*] Shields are quite a lot stronger
[/list]

[h2] Known Limitations [/h2]

[list]
    [*] Surveying with military ships only works with single ships (not with fleets)
[/list]

